Graph_Theory.Collatz sequence:
For a given integer value n, the sequence of numbers that derives from performing the following computatin on n
while (n > 1)
 if (ODD(n))
    n = 3 * n + 1;

 else    n = n / 2;This is famous because, while it terminates for any value of n that you try, it has never been proven to be a fact that this always terminates.
